  "prompt": "How do you become an electrical engineer?",
  "response": "To become an electrical engineer, follow these steps:\n\n1. Educational Requirements\n- Earn a bachelor's degree in electrical engineering from an accredited university\n- Focus on mathematics, physics, and engineering courses\n- Consider specializing in areas like power systems, electronics, or telecommunications\n\n2. Academic Preparation\n- Take advanced math and science classes in high school\n- Maintain a strong GPA\n- Participate in science and engineering clubs or competitions\n\n3. Degree Program\n- Complete a 4-year Bachelor of Science in Electrical Engineering (BSEE)\n- Take courses in circuit design, digital systems, signal processing\n- Participate in laboratory and hands-on engineering projects\n\n4. Gain Practical Experience\n- Complete internships during college\n- Participate in co-op programs\n- Work on research projects with professors\n\n5. Professional Certification\n- Pass the Fundamentals of Engineering (FE) exam\n- Gain work experience\n- Pass the Professional Engineer (PE) license exam\n\n6. Optional Advanced Education\n- Consider a master's or doctoral degree for advanced positions\n- Specialize in specific areas of electrical engineering\n\n7. Continuous Learning\n- Stay updated on technological advancements\n- Attend workshops and professional development seminars\n- Join professional organizations like IEEE",
